WEBVTT

00:01:28.167 --> 00:01:32.208
An older black American man said,
"Ain't no ambulance coming."

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:35.684
He said it again loudly to the cop.

00:01:35.708 --> 00:01:37.893
"You know ain't no ambulance coming.

00:01:37.917 --> 00:01:40.083
They never send no ambulance here."

00:01:41.083 --> 00:01:44.601
The cop looked at my neighbors
who were getting frustrated,

00:01:44.625 --> 00:01:46.559
lifted the girl into the patrol car

00:01:46.583 --> 00:01:48.018
and left.

00:01:48.042 --> 00:01:50.351
I was 10 years old at the time.

00:01:50.375 --> 00:01:52.184
I knew this wasn't right.

00:01:52.208 --> 00:01:54.601
I knew there was something
more we could do.

00:01:54.625 --> 00:01:57.226
The something I could do
was become a doctor.

00:01:57.250 --> 00:01:58.559
I became an internist

00:01:58.583 --> 00:02:02.934
and committed my career to caring
for those we often call the underserved,